In this project, I analyzed a sales dataset using Power BI. First, I imported the data and performed data cleaning using Power Query. 
Then, I created calculated columns such as Profit and Return Flag, and combined customer names to create a full name column.
I developed important measures like Total Sales, Total Profit, Return Rate, and Average Sale using DAX. 
To understand filter behavior, I applied functions like CALCULATE(), ALL(), and FILTER(). 
I used RELATED() to fetch data from related tables and implemented Time Intelligence functions such as SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR() for yearly 
comparison and running totals.
Finally, I created a Matrix visual to display sales data by Region, Product Category, and Customer Segment across months and years. 
This project helped me understand data modeling, DAX functions, and data visualization in Power BI.
